r\n`WindowSummaryTransformer`\r\n\r\nparameters:\r\n* `window_type: \"sliding\" (default) or \"expanding\"`\r\n* `window_size: int or datetime.timedelta`\r\n* `agg_func: str or function; if str, one of \"mean\", \"max\", \"min\", \"median\"; if function, must be pd.DataFrame (n rows) -> pd.DataFrame (one row)`\r\n* `lags: list of int`, list of lags that are used.\r\n\r\n`fit` is empty.\r\nIn `transform(X)`, computes `agg_func` of each window (ending at any index in `X`) and appends the results to a `pd.DataFrame`. The index of the `agg_func` output is identical with the index at which the window ends.\r\n\r\n\r\nMight also be worthwhile to have a `LagTransformer`, which has only the `lags` parameter?","closed_by":{"login":"fkiraly","id":7985502,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjc5ODU1MDI=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/7985502?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/fkiraly","html_url":"https://github.com/fkiraly","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/fkiraly/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/fkiraly/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/fkiraly/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/fkiraly/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/fkiraly/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/fkiraly/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/fkiraly/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/fkiraly/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/fkiraly/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sktime/sktime/issues/1581/reactions","total_count":1,"+1":1,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sktime/sktime/issues/1581/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed"}